55-year-oid Adelakin Adeniyi on Wednesday bagged three years imprisonment for forging Magistrates’ Court stamp. Magistrate Habibat Basiru of an Osun State Magistrates’ Court who convicted Adelakin Adeniyi said the prosecutor proved his case beyond reasonable doubt. The convict was arraigned on Jan 9, 2019 and pleaded not guilty to two-count charge of conspiracy and forgery, but changed the plea to guilty on Feb 4, 2020, while the fact of the case was presented yesterday. Magistrate Habibat Basiru sentenced Adeniyi to three years imprisonment on each count but added that the jail term would run consecutively without an option of fine. The police prosecutor, Joseph Adebayo, an Assistant Superintendent of Police told the court that Adelakin Adeniyi, committed the offence on Dec 10, 2018 around 10:00 am at Ile-Ife. Adebayo said that the convict conspired together with others now at large to commit felony to wit: forgery. He added that the convict forged High Court Affidavit stamp, Ife East Local Government Marriage Registry Stamp and stamp of Osun State Magistrates’ court, Ile-Ife. According to him, the offence contravened sections 465, 467 and 516 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Osun, 2002. 